A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 34-4-3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 amount of minimum wage to be paid by employers, so as to increase the state minimum
3 wage to a living wage; to provide for related matters; to provide for a short title; to repeal
4 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Vincent Fort Living Wage Act."
8 SECTION 2.
9 Code Section 34-4-3 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to amount of
10 minimum wage to be paid by employers, is amended by revising subsection (a) as follows:
11 "(a) Except as otherwise provided in this Code section, every employer, whether a person,
12 firm, or corporation, shall pay to all covered employees a minimum wage which shall be
13 not less than $5.15 $15.00 per hour for each hour worked in the employment of such
14 employer."
